pr_review_comment_body:
It seems to work as of OS X 10.11:

```
% cat fdopendir.c
#include <dirent.h>
#include <fcntl.h>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <unistd.h>

int main(int argc, char** argv) {
  int fd = open("/", 0);
  if (fd == -1) {
    perror("open");
    return 1;
  }
  DIR *dir = fdopendir(fd);
  if (dir == NULL) {
    perror("fdopendir");
    return 1;
  }
  struct dirent *dp;
  while ((dp = readdir(dir)) != NULL) {
    printf("%s\n", dp->d_name);
  }
  closedir(dir);
  close(fd);
  return 0;
}

% clang -isysroot /Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.11.sdk -o fdopendir fdopendir.c
% ./fdopendir
.
..
(snip a bunch of stuff)
```

minor: Since equality is delegated upwards to `URL`, would it be better to do the same for hashing?

e.g.

```python
def __hash__(self):
    return hash(self.normalize().to_uri())
```

@jwhui I moved this definition to platform-config.h by the last change of #2719, sorry that I didn't verify it since I didn't expect the definitions in platform-config.h don't take effect in aes_alt.h.

But if I include platform-config.h in aes_alt.h, there are some build errors like:
```
  CXX      api/libopenthread_mtd_a-commissioner_api.o
In file included from /home/chenshu/code/openthread/examples/../third_party/NordicSemiconductor/libraries/crypto/aes_alt.h:55:0,
                 from /home/chenshu/code/openthread/examples/../third_party/mbedtls/repo.patched/include/mbedtls/aes.h:325,
                 from /home/chenshu/code/openthread/examples/../third_party/mbedtls/repo.patched/include/mbedtls/ctr_drbg.h:26,
                 from /home/chenshu/code/openthread/examples/../src/core/meshcop/dtls.hpp:42,
                 from /home/chenshu/code/openthread/examples/../src/core/coap/coap_secure.hpp:35,
                 from /home/chenshu/code/openthread/examples/../src/core/thread/thread_netif.hpp:42,
                 from /home/chenshu/code/openthread/examples/../src/core/common/instance.hpp:61,
                 from /home/chenshu/code/openthread/examples/../src/core/api/border_router_api.cpp:40:
/home/chenshu/code/openthread/examples/../examples/platforms/nrf52840/platform-config.h:40:10: fatal error: drivers/clock/nrf_drv_clock.h: No such file or directory
 #include "drivers/clock/nrf_drv_clock.h"
```

The build error is because that the header files in third_party library is not visible to OT core.

So I move this definition back here, and it works now. Please let know if you have any concern about this way, thanks.
